## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the React + Vite project following the latest official documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart.

### Changes Made:

**1. Installed Package**
- Added `@vercel/analytics` (v2.0.1) to dependencies
- Updated package-lock.json with new dependencies

**2. Modified Files**
- `frontend/src/App.jsx`: Added Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
  - Imported Analytics component at the top of the file
  - Added `<Analytics />` component within the AuthProvider, after Routes component
  - This ensures analytics tracking across all routes while maintaining the existing app structure

**3. Verified**
- Build completed successfully with no errors
- No linting or test errors (project doesn't have lint/test scripts configured)
- All changes follow the official Vercel documentation for React/Vite projects

### Implementation Details:

The Analytics component was placed inside the AuthProvider but outside Routes to ensure:
- Analytics loads on all pages
- Tracking works across route transitions
- Component hierarchy and context providers remain intact

### Next Steps for User:

To complete the analytics setup:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel (`vercel deploy`)
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
3. Verify tracking by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/view` after deployment

The implementation follows the React/Vite framework-specific instructions from the official documentation and preserves all existing code structure and functionality.
